I agree with you Aphroditex. However, that is not the issue. The issue is over public officials (including elected officials) who pray in public over "captured audiences". That is a form of intimidation, and is an abuse of power. Both of which are not protected by the constitution as free speech. <p><center><font face="arial" color="CCFFFF">Lurikeen Mali'Kyre</FONT></center><center><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#150517, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='Necromancer'><font size=2 color="red" face="arial"><i>NECROMANCER</span></td></tr></table></font></i></center><center><font face=arial></center><center><I>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"</I></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uaphroditex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphroditex</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#E9D756>(6/1/02 9:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waaaaaazup!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The issue is over public officials (including elected officials) who pray in public over &quot;captured audiences&quot;. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
But in the excerpt it stated very clearly that the audience wasn't captive, it stated that many of the senators got up and walked out.  The priest chose to pray in public, the senators that didn't want to hear it chose to leave.  No one locked them in the room and chained them to their seats to force them to listen.<br>
<br>
As for the scripture that you quoted, Jesus does not say that praying in public is wrong, he simply says that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> the reasons</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for which some people pray in public are not the reasons for which you <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> should</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be praying.  You should be praying for forgiveness and a bond with God, not for the admiration/acceptance of men.  As with all his teachings, Jesus provided the people with a way to be secure in knowing you are praying for the right reasons when he suggested that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;when you pray, go into your room, close the door and pray to your Father, who is unseen. Then your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  He was not saying that praying in public is wrong, he was simply saying that you would be secure in knowing (as God knows) that when you pray in private, you are doing it for the right reasons.  This was more a lesson to teach praying for the correct reason than a lesson denouncing prayer in public. <p>________________________________________________________<BR><a href><font color=#CC90FF><i><b>"I am a Child of the Universe.  With a glitter of my life I travel through black, velvet space, and the gates of time.  I am a star awoken from it's sleep - by the longing cries of mankind's dreams.  Dreams of harmony, love, and a Child of the Universe."</b></i></font></a><BR>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165032"><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jwebb2/Serenity.jpg" width="109" height="230"></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=164717"><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jwebb2/Pickett.jpg" width="89" height="230"></a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165042"><img border="0" src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jwebb2/Aphroditex.jpg" width="110" height="230"></a><BR>Click on a character to see their profile.<BR><a href><font face="Monotype Corsiva" color="#FF7000" size=4><b>Member of Anlah'shok</font></b></font></a><BR>
