An atheist has no belief in gods, but I don't think you can call &quot;nonbelief&quot; a belief system and definitely not a religion.  I think Lurikeen was just noting that there are many more players in the field like agnostics, new agers, eastern religions, etc.<br>
<br>
I think the larger issue is that religion is very bad at trying to enforce others to follow its dogma.  James Madison studied to become a minister but ended up speaking out against separation of church and state.  At that time in Virginia, you could receive the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> death penality</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> for speaking impiously of any articles of Christianity, blaspheming God's name or incorrigible cursing.  Very scary.<br>
