<br>
By praying aloud you are telling someone &quot;this is what I believe&quot;. You are not telling someone &quot;you are wrong.&quot; We honor all faiths in this country,  therefore it is perfectly ok to express your own personal beliefs as long as you do not criticize someone else's.<br>
<br>
Praying in the senate is telling everyone &quot;this is my faith&quot; and is not a denouncement of other faiths or beliefs.<br>
